2026-03-07 | Minimum Flips to Make Binary String Alternating with Rotations

	Question
Return the minimum number of flips (type-2 operations) needed to make the string alternating, considering you can rotate the string any number of times.

	Approach
1.	Since rotations are allowed, treat the string as circular.
2.	Create a doubled string:
		s + s
3.	The alternating patterns possible are:
		pattern1: 010101...
		pattern2: 101010...
4.	Use sliding window of size n over the doubled string.
5.	Count mismatches with both patterns inside the window.
6.	As the window slides:
		remove the left character mismatch
		add the new right character mismatch.
7.	Track the minimum flips needed.

	Time Complexity
	O(n)

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int minFlips(string s) {
        int n = s.size();
        string t = s + s;

        int ans = INT_MAX;
        int diff1 = 0, diff2 = 0;
        int left = 0;

        for (int right = 0; right < t.size(); right++) {
            char expected1 = (right % 2) ? '1' : '0';
            char expected2 = (right % 2) ? '0' : '1';

            if (t[right] != expected1) diff1++;
            if (t[right] != expected2) diff2++;

            if (right - left + 1 > n) {
                char exp1 = (left % 2) ? '1' : '0';
                char exp2 = (left % 2) ? '0' : '1';

                if (t[left] != exp1) diff1--;
                if (t[left] != exp2) diff2--;
                left++;
            }

            if (right - left + 1 == n)
                ans = min(ans, min(diff1, diff2));
        }

        return ans;
    }
};

	Key Insight
Rotations make the string circular.
By doubling the string and sliding a window of size n,
we evaluate every possible rotation.
Counting mismatches with the two valid alternating patterns
gives the minimum flips needed.
